<dec f='include/python2.7/unicodeobject.h' l='259' type='PyObject * PyUnicodeUCS4_DecodeUTF16(const char * string, Py_ssize_t length, const char * errors, int * byteorder)'/>
<doc f='include/python2.7/unicodeobject.h' l='849'>/* Decodes length bytes from a UTF-16 encoded buffer string and returns
   the corresponding Unicode object.

   errors (if non-NULL) defines the error handling. It defaults
   to &quot;strict&quot;.

   If byteorder is non-NULL, the decoder starts decoding using the
   given byte order:

    *byteorder == -1: little endian
    *byteorder == 0:  native order
    *byteorder == 1:  big endian

   In native mode, the first two bytes of the stream are checked for a
   BOM mark. If found, the BOM mark is analysed, the byte order
   adjusted and the BOM skipped.  In the other modes, no BOM mark
   interpretation is done. After completion, *byteorder is set to the
   current byte order at the end of input data.

   If byteorder is NULL, the codec starts in native order mode.

*/</doc>
